  <summary date="2017-05-18T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Private Student Loan Bankruptcy Fairness Act of 2017 

This bill amends the federal bankruptcy code to allow&#160;private education loans to be discharged in bankruptcy&#160;regardless of whether&#160;a debtor&#160;demonstrates&#160;undue hardship.&#160;Under current law,&#160;student loans may be discharged in bankruptcy only if the loans impose an undue hardship on the debtor.</summary>
